Winds out of the SE at 5 mph with 20 % cloud cover.  Algal bloom status was low.  TP only at a depth of 0.5 meters.  "TP only - Prior windy and cold snap".
No Cloud cover with winds out of the SE at 10-20 mph.  No algal bloom evident.  Water chemistry and Chla sampled with integrated sampler (0.5 meters).
5% cloud cover with winds at 5mph.  TMDL suite sampled at 0.5 meters (Integrated sampler) with NO2 and NO3 added.  Alagal bloom was extensive and dense.

Winds out of the east at 15 mph with 100% cloud cover.  Water color green.  No profiles taken due to time and wavers.  TMDL suite samples with an Integrated sampler.  No prior rain.  Algal bloom obvious.
WN1 - 40% Cloud cover- 70 F- N wind at 15-20 mph.  Samples collected for TMDL suite.  Bright green algal bloom present.  Rough water/ waves at 1-3'- profile only to 1 meter.

30% cloud cover with winds out of the S. at 20 mph and no prior rain.  TMDL suite sampled with integrated sampler.  Water pea green in color with an obvious algal bloom and was lighter than the southern Bago sites.
